---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Commercial Photography for Businesses | Adam Barnes, Suffolk"
  description="Brand, event, product and architecture photography from the web designer who builds your site. One supplier, images made for the layout. Norfolk & Suffolk."
  canonical="https://www.adambarnes.biz/photography.html"
  ogImage="https://www.adambarnes.biz/assets/og-photography.jpg"
  bodyClass="page-photography"
  active="photography"
  breadcrumbLabel="Photography"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
{
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Service",
    "@id": "https://www.adambarnes.biz/photography.html#service",
    "name": "Commercial Photography by Adam Barnes",
    "provider": {
      "@type": "Person",
      "@id": "https://www.adambarnes.biz/#person",
      "name": "Adam Barnes",
      "url": "https://www.adambarnes.biz"
    },
    "serviceType": "Commercial Photography",
    "description": "Commercial photography for businesses, from the web designer who builds their site. Brand portraiture, events, product, food and architecture across Norfolk, Suffolk and the UK. One supplier, images art-directed for the layout and sized for performance.",
    "areaServed": [
      "Norfolk",
      "Suffolk",
      "United Kingdom"
    ],
    "hasOfferCatalog": {
      "@type": "OfferCatalog",
      "name": "Commercial Photography Services",
      "itemListElement": [
        {
          "@type": "Offer",
          "itemOffered": {
            "@type": "Service",
            "name": "Brand & Headshot Photography",
            "description": "You and your team, photographed like humans rather than LinkedIn cutouts."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Offer",
          "itemOffered": {
            "@type": "Service",
            "name": "Event & Conference Photography",
            "description": "Coverage that catches the room, not just the podium."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Offer",
          "itemOffered": {
            "@type": "Service",
            "name": "Product & Food Photography",
            "description": "Product and food photographed with the same care they were made."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Offer",
          "itemOffered": {
            "@type": "Service",
            "name": "Architecture & Premises Photography",
            "description": "Buildings, workshops and shopfronts at their best."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    "url": "https://www.adambarnes.biz/photography.html"
  }
  </script>
  </Fragment>

<main>
    <!-- Hero (unchanged heading) with new business-facing opening -->
    <header class="section-header photography-header">
      <h1 class="section-title">
        <span>Inspired</span>
        <span class="accent">Photo<wbr>graphy</span>
        <span class="by-line">by Adam</span>
      </h1>
      <h2 class="intro-lead" style="max-width: 630px;">A shoot usually ends with a handover: a folder of images, and a website that has to make the best of them. Mine ends with images that already know where they're going.</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">I'm a web designer who shoots, which is rarer than it should be. When I photograph your business, I'm already thinking about the hero image, the crop at mobile widths, the space your headline will need. The photograph and the page it lives on are designed by the same pair of eyes.</p>
    </header>

    <!-- Body: one-supplier story + service menu, in the service-page language -->
    <section class="cs-body reveal" aria-label="Why one supplier">
      <div class="cs-body-inner">
        <div class="cs-copy">
          <div class="cs-copy-col">
            <h2 class="cs-copy-heading">One supplier, no gaps</h2>
            <p>When <a href="case-study-tom-appleton.html">Tom Appleton</a> needed a website, we didn't start with a design. We started with a shoot. An afternoon at a café table, talking, while I photographed him doing what he actually does: listening, thinking, explaining. Those photographs shaped the site, not the other way round.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-copy-col">
            <h2 class="cs-copy-heading">The quiet advantage</h2>
            <p>Hiring one person for both means no brief lost in translation between a designer and a photographer who have never met. No stock images pretending to be your business. No mystery over who owns what, because you own the lot. And because every image is sized and compressed for the build from day one, the site stays fast, which Google notices and your visitors feel.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <blockquote class="cs-quote">
          <p>You can hire me to shoot with no website attached. Plenty of people do. But when the two come together, that's when it earns its keep.</p>
        </blockquote>

        <div class="cs-copy" style="margin-top:2.5rem;">
          <div class="cs-copy-col">
            <h2 class="cs-copy-heading">What I shoot for businesses</h2>
            <p>Four things, mostly. All aimed at how your business actually looks to the people you want to reach.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-copy-col">
            <ul class="cs-list">
              <li><strong>Brand and headshot days.</strong> You and your team, photographed like humans rather than LinkedIn cutouts.</li>
              <li><strong>Events and conferences.</strong> Coverage that catches the room, not just the podium.</li>
              <li><strong>Product and food.</strong> Things made carefully deserve to be photographed carefully.</li>
              <li><strong>Architecture and premises.</strong> Your building, your workshop, your shopfront, at their best.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Curated strip: ten frames, existing grid component, contained -->
    <section class="gallery-section reveal" aria-label="Selected work">
      <div class="cs-body-inner" style="padding-bottom:0;">
        <h2 class="cs-copy-heading">Selected work</h2>
        <p class="section-intro" style="margin-top:0.25rem;">A few frames from the working portfolio.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="photo-grid photo-grid--strip">
        <div class="photo-item"><a href="https://www.adambarnesphotos.co.uk/portfolio/commercial" target="_blank" rel="noopener" aria-label="View the full commercial photography gallery on adambarnesphotos.co.uk"><img src="assets/photography/commercial/DSCF0190.webp" width="1700" height="723" alt="Black and white candid photograph of Tom Appleton in conversation over coffee at a café table, a bakery shopfront visible through the window behind" loading="lazy"></a><div class="photo-overlay"><span class="photo-caption">Tom Appleton</span><span class="photo-overlay-link">View full gallery →</span></div></div>
        <div class="photo-item"><a href="https://www.adambarnesphotos.co.uk/portfolio/food" target="_blank" rel="noopener" aria-label="View the full food photography gallery on adambarnesphotos.co.uk"><img src="assets/photography/Food/DSCF0152-RAF_DxO_DeepPRIME-Edit.webp" width="1200" height="800" alt="Five painted chocolate domes on a marble surface" loading="lazy"></a><div class="photo-overlay"><span class="photo-caption">Chocolate domes</span><span class="photo-overlay-link">View full gallery →</span></div></div>
        <div class="photo-item"><a href="https://www.adambarnesphotos.co.uk/portfolio/music-event" target="_blank" rel="noopener" aria-label="View the full music events gallery on adambarnesphotos.co.uk"><img src="assets/photography/music-events/XH2X2974.webp" width="1200" height="800" alt="Nile Rodgers performing on stage at Latitude Festival" loading="lazy"></a><div class="photo-overlay"><span class="photo-caption">Nile Rodgers at Latitude</span><span class="photo-overlay-link">View full gallery →</span></div></div>        <div class="photo-item"><a href="https://www.adambarnesphotos.co.uk/portfolio/commercial" target="_blank" rel="noopener" aria-label="View the full commercial photography gallery on adambarnesphotos.co.uk"><img src="assets/photography/commercial/DSCF0386-RAF_DxO_DeepPRIME.webp" width="1134" height="1700" alt="Gary Hunter of Hunter Chocolates in white chef's jacket pouring liquid chocolate from a bowl onto a white curved surface, caught mid-pour with intense concentration" loading="lazy"></a><div class="photo-overlay"><span class="photo-caption">Gary Hunter, chocolate pouring</span><span class="photo-overlay-link">View full gallery →</span></div></div>
        <div class="photo-item"><a href="https://www.adambarnesphotos.co.uk/portfolio/commercial" target="_blank" rel="noopener" aria-label="View the full commercial photography gallery on adambarnesphotos.co.uk"><img src="assets/photography/commercial/DSCF3284.webp" width="1700" height="1134" alt="Black and white photograph of Brian Bush and Cassandra Andrews presenting together at an Engaging Norfolk event, addressing a seated audience" loading="lazy"></a><div class="photo-overlay"><span class="photo-caption">Engaging Norfolk, Brian Bush and Cassandra Andrews</span><span class="photo-overlay-link">View full gallery →</span></div></div>
        <div class="photo-item"><a href="https://www.adambarnesphotos.co.uk/portfolio/commercial" target="_blank" rel="noopener" aria-label="View the full commercial photography gallery on adambarnesphotos.co.uk"><img src="assets/photography/commercial/DSCF0021-2-2-RAF_DxO_DeepPRIME.webp" width="1700" height="796" alt="Extreme close-up of plastic chips cascading through industrial recycling machinery at IPE's recycling plant, motion blur capturing the flow of material" loading="lazy"></a><div class="photo-overlay"><span class="photo-caption">IPE Recycling Plant</span><span class="photo-overlay-link">View full gallery →</span></div></div>
        <div class="photo-item"><a href="https://www.adambarnesphotos.co.uk/portfolio/portraits" target="_blank" rel="noopener" aria-label="View the full portraits gallery on adambarnesphotos.co.uk"><img src="assets/photography/Portrait/DSCF7357.webp" width="800" height="1200" alt="Poet George Szirtes reading on stage at First Light Festival, Lowestoft" loading="lazy"></a><div class="photo-overlay"><span class="photo-caption">George Szirtes, First Light Festival</span><span class="photo-overlay-link">View full gallery →</span></div></div>
        <div class="photo-item"><a href="https://www.adambarnesphotos.co.uk/portfolio/architecture" target="_blank" rel="noopener" aria-label="View the full architecture gallery on adambarnesphotos.co.uk"><img src="assets/photography/architecture/IMG_1892.webp" width="1200" height="830" alt="Aerial black and white view looking straight down the spiral staircase of the Queen's House, Greenwich, its perfect circular geometry set against a deep black background" loading="lazy"></a><div class="photo-overlay"><span class="photo-caption">Queen's House Spiral</span><span class="photo-overlay-link">View full gallery →</span></div></div>
        <div class="photo-item"><a href="https://www.adambarnesphotos.co.uk/portfolio/architecture" target="_blank" rel="noopener" aria-label="View the full architecture gallery on adambarnesphotos.co.uk"><img src="assets/photography/architecture/DSCF0727.webp" width="1700" height="1133" alt="Modern atrium interior at the Olympic Village, London, steeply angled roof with parallel LED strip lighting and a warm amber-lit rectangular wall feature below" loading="lazy"></a><div class="photo-overlay"><span class="photo-caption">Olympic Village Atrium</span><span class="photo-overlay-link">View full gallery →</span></div></div>
        <div class="photo-item"><a href="https://www.adambarnesphotos.co.uk/portfolio/commercial" target="_blank" rel="noopener" aria-label="View the full commercial photography gallery on adambarnesphotos.co.uk"><img src="assets/photography/commercial/DSCF0716.webp" width="1700" height="998" alt="Nic Pendlebury of Sonic Collaborations with a brass and wind ensemble of around fifteen musicians posing outdoors in front of the Old Royal Naval College, Greenwich at dusk, instruments in hand" loading="lazy"></a><div class="photo-overlay"><span class="photo-caption">Nic Pendlebury, Sonic Collaborations</span><span class="photo-overlay-link">View full gallery →</span></div></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Closing: portfolio anchor text + two CTAs, service-page two-column -->
    <section class="cs-body reveal" aria-label="See more">
      <div class="cs-body-inner">
        <div class="cs-copy">
          <div class="cs-copy-col">
            <h2 class="cs-copy-heading">The full portfolio</h2>
            <p>The full body of work lives at <a href="https://www.adambarnesphotos.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">adambarnesphotos.co.uk</a>: festivals, architecture, portraits, and the personal projects that keep the eye sharp. If your business needs photographing properly, tell me what you're trying to say.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-copy-col">
            <h2 class="cs-copy-heading">Ready when you are</h2>
            <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; align-items:flex-start; gap:0.9rem; margin-top:0.6rem;">
              <a href="https://www.adambarnesphotos.co.uk" class="btn-cta" target="_blank" rel="noopener">See the full portfolio →</a>
              <a href="https://www.adambarnesphotos.co.uk/hire" class="btn-cta" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Book a shoot →</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</Base>
